===Analysis===
'''Kuma Kai'''

Priority: '''Low'''

:At first remodel, she has good Firepower and Torpedo stat for a light cruiser, meaning she can do [[Artillery Spotting]] with decent damage at day and packs a good punch at night, too.
:Her ASW stat also allow her to perform OASW attacks with proper setup.

'''Kuma Kai Ni'''

Priority: '''Low-Medium'''

:On her second remodel, she has good Firepower and Torpedo stat for a light cruiser, meaning she can do [[Artillery Spotting]] with decent damage at day and packs a good punch at night, too.
:Her ASW stat also allow her to perform OASW attacks with proper setup.
:The main perk of this form is the ability to equip Seaplane Fighters which can help reach desired air-power levels. Slot sizes are too small to get any real use out of Seaplane Bombers.

'''Kuma Kai Ni D'''

Priority: '''Medium-High'''

:Her third remodel lowers her torpedo stat and a small amount of firepower which takes her back down to average in these areas.
:She makes up for these stat losses by gaining the ability to equip mini-subs to launch opening torpedo strikes.
:The ability to equip landing craft and tanks also helps her to deal with installation-type enemies.
:Her ASW stat is slightly increased, allowing her to perform OASW attacks a bit more easily.

====Recommended Roles====
* Surface combat
* ASW

===Important Info===
* Required for A58, A74, B52, B85, and B163.

